    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmNotes": "<p><em>&lt;@Compendium[sfrpg.rules.GnEF27Oot3zqTaBQ]{Diseases}</em></p>\n<p><em>Track the progress in the details tab in \"Base Value\". 0; Healthy, 3; Stiffened.</em></p>\n<p><em>To keep the affliction type a secret, renaming the item is suggested. This does not prevent the player from looking at the details tab to learn the affliction type.</em></p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-underline-header);\">Leprosy</h2>\n<p><strong>Type&nbsp;</strong>disease (contact, inhaled, or injury);&nbsp;<strong>Save&nbsp;</strong>Fortitude DC 12<br /><strong>Track&nbsp;</strong>physical (special);&nbsp;<strong>Frequency&nbsp;</strong>1/week<br /><strong>Effect&nbsp;</strong>progression track is Healthy&mdash;Latent&mdash;Sluggish&mdash;Stiffened; sluggish and stiffened are as per the Dexterity poison track states; stiffened is the end state.<br /><strong>Cure&nbsp;</strong>2 consecutive saves</p>\n<p><em>Modifiers currently do not effect Ability DCs</em></p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-underline-header);\">Disease Track</h2>\n<p><strong>Healthy&mdash;Latent&mdash;Sluggish</strong><strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">&mdash;</strong><strong>Stiffened&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<h3>Latent</h3>\n<p>The victim has contracted a disease. She suffers no ill effects yet, but if the disease is contagious, she can pass it on.</p>\n<h3>Sluggish</h3>\n<p>The victim takes a &ndash;2 penalty to Reflex saves and Dexterity-based ability checks, attack rolls, and skill checks; the DCs of her spells and special abilities decrease by 2; and she becomes @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.MZ8OoH1GE9qDMyCD]{Flat-Footed}.</p>\n<h3>Stiffened</h3>\n<p>The victim loses her Dexterity bonus to her Armor Class, and she can&rsquo;t take reactions.</p>",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p><em>&lt;@Compendium[sfrpg.rules.JaRMioj4isNp7r1P]{Afflictions}</em></p>\n<p><em>The GM may find the Affliction's details in the GM Notes tab of this item.</em></p>"
    },
